<blockquote>[B][SIZE=4]Wether you used this or not, post or i will have this removed![/SIZE][/B]
By default it is impossible to make transparent areas in an image and load them into your client, this would make all transparent parts of an image appear as white once the client is loaded.
Finnaly i've found a way around this, that allows transparent images to stay transparent in the client.

Simple, replace your method349 in Class30_Sub2_Sub1_Sub1.java with this one:
[code]    public void method349(int ai[], int ai1[], int i, int j, int k, int l, int i1, 
            int j1, int k1)
    {
        int l1 = -(l >> 2);
        l = -(l & 3);
        for(int i2 = -i1; i2 < 0; i2++)
        {
            for(int j2 = l1; j2 < 0; j2++)
            {
                i = ai1[j++];
                if(i != 0 && i != -1)
                {
                    ai[k++] = i;
                } else
                {
                    k++;
                }
                i = ai1[j++];
                if(i != 0 && i != -1)
                {
                    ai[k++] = i;
                } else
                {
                    k++;
                }
                i = ai1[j++];
                if(i != 0 && i != -1)
                {
                    ai[k++] = i;
                } else
                {
                    k++;
                }
                i = ai1[j++];
                if(i != 0 && i != -1)
                {
                    ai[k++] = i;
                } else
                {
                    k++;
                }
            }

            for(int k2 = l; k2 < 0; k2++)
            {
                i = ai1[j++];
                if(i != 0 && i != -1)
                {
                    ai[k++] = i;
                } else
                {
                    k++;
                }
            }

            k += j1;
            j += k1;
        }

    }[/code]Use white in the image as the transparent part.
For white, use color RBG[254, 254, 254] or HEX[FEFEFE].</blockquote>

